1
00:00:06,042 --> 00:00:08,767
♫  I want to go to the future  ♫

2
00:00:08,767 --> 00:00:12,122
♫  I want to go to the future  ♫

3
00:00:12,122 --> 00:00:18,215
♫  I want to seize the day and put the whole world into my head  ♫

4
00:00:18,215 --> 00:00:24,541
♫  I want to go back in time to do all the crazy things I didn't do  ♫

5
00:00:24,541 --> 00:00:30,962
♫  Don't say goodbye, don't be in a daze, let my radiant light be bright  ♫

6
00:00:30,962 --> 00:00:35,948
♫  We are always looking forward to the unknown future  ♫

7
00:00:35,948 --> 00:00:43,248
♫  And often overlooking our surroundings and best plan in front of us  ♫

8
00:00:43,248 --> 00:00:48,272
♫  Every day my heart beats for you  ♫

9
00:00:48,272 --> 00:00:49,885
♫  Be your light  ♫

10
00:00:49,885 --> 00:00:55,648
♫  You are no doubt irreplaceable  ♫

11
00:00:55,648 --> 00:01:02,148
♫  Every day the sun shines through the window  ♫

12
00:01:02,148 --> 00:01:08,315
♫  With the reflection of you being my incredible highlight  ♫

13
00:01:08,315 --> 00:01:11,802
[I Don't Want to be Brothers with You]

14
00:01:17,882 --> 00:01:22,162
[Compound 2 of Oil Field Living Quarters]

15
00:03:02,922 --> 00:03:14,497
[Episode 21: If We Never Met]

16
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:20,880
Xiaowen, you're in the wrong place. This isn't your apartment. Let's go.

17
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,743
No, Xiaowen, it's really not your apartment.

18
00:04:03,740 --> 00:04:06,200
Xiaowen, let's go.

19
00:04:13,219 --> 00:04:15,719
There used to be a cabinet here.

20
00:04:19,219 --> 00:04:21,879
I loved candy when I was a child.

21
00:04:22,779 --> 00:04:25,979
My mom didn't want me to get cavities,

22
00:04:25,979 --> 00:04:29,040
so she hid the candies at the very top.

23
00:04:31,179 --> 00:04:36,500
I... I always stole the candies when they weren't looking.

24
00:04:39,209 --> 00:04:43,559
I was too young and I couldn't reach it.

25
00:04:51,099 --> 00:04:53,119
There was a sofa here.

26
00:04:53,119 --> 00:04:55,280
We were the only family

27
00:04:56,460 --> 00:04:59,360
with a spring sofa in the community

28
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:05,820
because it was made by my dad.

29
00:05:07,979 --> 00:05:10,020
The two of them

30
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:16,219
loved to read and tell stories to me on the sofa.

31
00:05:33,219 --> 00:05:35,400
The fan was here.

32
00:05:36,620 --> 00:05:38,979
In the summer,

33
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,779
I loved to sit on the wooden horse

34
00:05:42,779 --> 00:05:46,419
while my mom fed me watermelon.

35
00:05:46,419 --> 00:05:49,820
She sprinkled a lot of sugar on it.

36
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:53,380
It was really sweet.

37
00:05:55,959 --> 00:05:56,879
On the wall...

38
00:05:56,879 --> 00:06:00,979
There were our family photos on the wall.

39
00:06:00,979 --> 00:06:07,379
That burnt photo was hanging right there.

40
00:06:07,379 --> 00:06:12,439
Next to that was their graduation photo from the Beijing University of Technology.

41
00:06:19,820 --> 00:06:23,600
There was... also a closet over there.

42
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,739
I was childish then.

43
00:06:25,739 --> 00:06:29,704
I loved hiding in there to play hide and seek with them.

44
00:06:30,659 --> 00:06:32,579
Mom...

45
00:06:35,060 --> 00:06:36,439
Xiaowen.

46
00:06:36,439 --> 00:06:40,180
Dad, I'm home.

47
00:06:40,739 --> 00:06:43,359
I'm home.

48
00:06:43,359 --> 00:06:44,339
Xiaowen.

49
00:06:44,339 --> 00:06:46,274
Xiaowen, say no more.

50
00:06:48,460 --> 00:06:49,959
It's my fault.

51
00:06:49,959 --> 00:06:52,979
I didn't know it would turn out like this.

52
00:06:54,419 --> 00:06:57,439
I thought... there would be something left in here.

53
00:06:57,439 --> 00:07:00,359
There's nothing.

54
00:07:00,359 --> 00:07:02,539
They're all gone!

55
00:07:02,539 --> 00:07:04,379
They're both gone.

56
00:07:04,379 --> 00:07:05,779
I have no home.

57
00:07:05,779 --> 00:07:09,400
I have no parents anymore.

58
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,400
Mom.

59
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:15,359
Mom, I'm home.

60
00:07:15,359 --> 00:07:18,739
I'm home.

61
00:07:18,739 --> 00:07:23,959
I'm home. Where are you guys? Dad...

62
00:07:23,959 --> 00:07:26,820
Dad...

63
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:35,299
Xiaowen, I'm here.

64
00:07:37,199 --> 00:07:39,319
I'll always be here for you.

65
00:07:39,739 --> 00:07:41,920
Mom.

66
00:08:18,239 --> 00:08:21,280
Hello, my name is Gao Yang.

67
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:23,879
I'm glad to be your deskmate.

68
00:08:28,859 --> 00:08:31,339
Don't talk. We're in class.

69
00:08:41,539 --> 00:08:46,140
Xiaowen, I will train with you every morning from now on.

70
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:54,559
Focus on your studies first.

71
00:08:57,140 --> 00:08:58,459
Don't worry.

72
00:08:58,459 --> 00:09:00,419
I'll make sure to advance by 30 ranks in the next exam.

73
00:09:00,419 --> 00:09:02,819
I'm so smart, aren't I?

74
00:09:15,220 --> 00:09:18,539
I will never cheat again.

75
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:27,199
All right, I forgive you.

76
00:09:27,199 --> 00:09:29,959
I didn't take it to heart anyway.

77
00:09:29,959 --> 00:09:31,419
That won't do.

78
00:09:31,419 --> 00:09:35,379
You see, I even made a mistake with the train ticket.

79
00:09:35,379 --> 00:09:38,120
Enough, Gao Yang.

80
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:39,706
So childish.

81
00:09:41,559 --> 00:09:42,919
See?

82
00:09:42,919 --> 00:09:44,200
Isn't it nice to smile?

83
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:48,839
Therefore, you can't always keep everything to yourself.

84
00:09:48,839 --> 00:09:50,780
You have to say it out.

85
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:02,171
Thank you.

86
00:10:07,779 --> 00:10:09,341
Thank you.

87
00:10:15,699 --> 00:10:17,438
Actually...

88
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:21,640
I've always wanted to come home for a visit.

89
00:10:27,299 --> 00:10:29,061
But...

90
00:10:30,939 --> 00:10:33,260
But every time I...

91
00:10:35,419 --> 00:10:37,660
But every time I'm afraid.

92
00:10:37,660 --> 00:10:40,000
I... I'm afraid.

93
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:42,438
What's there to be afraid of?

94
00:10:42,438 --> 00:10:45,819
Well, Gao Yang is here.

95
00:10:46,779 --> 00:10:48,412
I will take care of you,

96
00:10:51,659 --> 00:10:53,108
right?

97
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:55,483
Who is it?

98
00:11:00,004 --> 00:11:01,545
Just kidding.

99
00:11:02,020 --> 00:11:04,687
I just want to scare you.

100
00:11:09,539 --> 00:11:10,901
Xiaowen,

101
00:11:11,859 --> 00:11:13,610
what is that?

102
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,379
Daddy, did I grow taller?

103
00:11:26,379 --> 00:11:28,586
Don't stand on your toes, Baby.

104
00:11:28,586 --> 00:11:30,960
Eyes forward, don't move.

105
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,220
Make me taller.

106
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:33,519
What's the rush?

107
00:11:33,519 --> 00:11:35,579
You'll grow up sooner or later.

108
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:37,879
Done.

109
00:11:37,879 --> 00:11:39,699
Xiaowen, you grew up so fast.

110
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:41,941
Here's last time and this time.

111
00:11:43,879 --> 00:11:45,320
Come here. Xiaowen, sit up here.

112
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:47,271
- Come here.
- Here we go.

113
00:11:48,620 --> 00:11:51,219
Three, two, one.

114
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:53,020
Wake up.

115
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:54,580
It's dawn.

116
00:11:54,580 --> 00:11:57,652
It's dawn.

117
00:12:00,819 --> 00:12:02,660
You're awake?

118
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:05,320
I wanted to let you sleep for a while longer,

119
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:08,679
but if we wait any longer, we'll miss the train.

120
00:12:10,179 --> 00:12:11,779
Do you want to stay here for a bit longer?

121
00:12:11,779 --> 00:12:13,742
I'll go out first.

122
00:12:15,740 --> 00:12:17,392
That's okay.

123
00:12:20,419 --> 00:12:21,914
Let's go.

124
00:12:48,260 --> 00:12:49,860
Dad,

125
00:12:49,860 --> 00:12:51,377
Mom,

126
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,086
goodbye.

127
00:13:08,639 --> 00:13:11,440
I spent all our money on this braised chicken.

128
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:13,665
Eat it now.

129
00:13:15,399 --> 00:13:18,719
Come on. Have a drumstick.

130
00:13:18,719 --> 00:13:22,679
Mr. Gao will surely be angry when we get home.

131
00:13:22,679 --> 00:13:24,753
Don't worry.

132
00:13:24,753 --> 00:13:27,848
No matter what happens, I'll take care of it.

133
00:13:27,848 --> 00:13:31,619
Passengers, please prepare your tickets for inspection.

134
00:13:31,619 --> 00:13:34,520
Passengers, please prepare your tickets for inspection.

135
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,699
I'll go wash my hands.

136
00:13:35,699 --> 00:13:37,599
The ticket is in my bag.

137
00:13:38,380 --> 00:13:40,299
Inside the big zipper.

138
00:14:25,419 --> 00:14:29,487
Still running? That's what you get for running away!

139
00:14:36,651 --> 00:14:39,620
How will we explain it later?

140
00:14:39,620 --> 00:14:41,100
What's there to explain?

141
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:43,479
We're home safe. What can he do?

142
00:14:43,479 --> 00:14:46,720
What if Mr. Gao asks us?

143
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:49,020
Don't say anything. Just take the beating.

144
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:50,498
Let's go.

145
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:01,780
Dad.

146
00:15:09,020 --> 00:15:10,059
How was it, Dad?

147
00:15:10,059 --> 00:15:12,184
Did I make a lot of mistakes this time?

148
00:15:12,759 --> 00:15:15,819
It's not bad this time.

149
00:15:27,179 --> 00:15:29,041
Did you hear that?

150
00:15:29,041 --> 00:15:30,459
You should be glad.

151
00:15:30,459 --> 00:15:33,740
You should be glad you're my daughter and not Gao Bin's.

152
00:15:33,740 --> 00:15:35,459
Look at how he disciplines his child.

153
00:15:35,459 --> 00:15:36,799
Just laugh up your sleeve.

154
00:15:36,799 --> 00:15:38,939
Dad, why don't you go persuade him?

155
00:15:38,939 --> 00:15:42,060
Something will go wrong if he keeps beating them.

156
00:15:57,620 --> 00:16:00,260
What exactly did you guys do yesterday?

157
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:03,060
Did you work at a construction site? How did you get it so dirty?

158
00:16:03,060 --> 00:16:05,020
We didn't go anywhere.

159
00:16:05,020 --> 00:16:06,179
Who are you trying to fool?

160
00:16:06,179 --> 00:16:07,659
Do you take me as a child?

161
00:16:07,659 --> 00:16:10,387
You won't tell me the truth, right? Do another fifty.

162
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,119
Get up.

163
00:16:20,119 --> 00:16:22,060
I can't get up.

164
00:16:22,060 --> 00:16:23,459
I'll do it for him.

165
00:16:23,459 --> 00:16:25,348
You want to do push-ups for him?

166
00:16:25,348 --> 00:16:29,140
Fine, Xiaowen, you'll do another two hundred.

167
00:16:29,140 --> 00:16:30,577
Okay.

168
00:16:31,739 --> 00:16:33,860
There's no need. I can do it.

169
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:35,743
Don't act tough.

170
00:16:36,299 --> 00:16:38,459
Are you looking down upon me?

171
00:16:38,459 --> 00:16:40,459
Not bad, you two.

172
00:16:40,459 --> 00:16:44,540
You've developed a good friendship over the trip?

173
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:47,479
I'm telling you, "leniency shall be given if you confess. Severe punishments shall come if you resist."

174
00:16:47,479 --> 00:16:50,579
If you don't tell the truth, you'll have salt for dinner!

175
00:17:13,872 --> 00:17:17,212
A-Auntie, what's wrong?

176
00:17:17,212 --> 00:17:19,060
W-Why did you ask me back in such a hurry?

177
00:17:19,060 --> 00:17:20,340
Did I affect your training?

178
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:22,979
No, it's about to end.

179
00:17:22,979 --> 00:17:24,300
- What happened?
- That's good.

180
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:25,755
Come here.

181
00:17:26,215 --> 00:17:27,860
Come here.

182
00:17:27,860 --> 00:17:29,699
I have something to tell you.

183
00:17:29,699 --> 00:17:31,739
Stay calm, okay?

184
00:17:31,739 --> 00:17:37,360
Didn't we get a lot of calls from someone who wouldn't say anything?

185
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:39,919
Those calls were from your dad.

186
00:17:39,919 --> 00:17:41,240
H-He's back?

187
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:44,240
Well, W-Where is he?

188
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:46,348
I don't know where he is.

189
00:17:46,348 --> 00:17:49,679
He just calls secretly and refuses to show up.

190
00:17:49,679 --> 00:17:51,060
But it's definitely him.

191
00:17:51,060 --> 00:17:53,980
With that voice, I can tell it's him right away.

192
00:17:53,980 --> 00:17:59,239
B-B-But, A-A-Auntie, w-w-what should we do now?

193
00:17:59,239 --> 00:18:00,559
How will we find him?

194
00:18:00,559 --> 00:18:02,259
Jia, stay calm.

195
00:18:02,259 --> 00:18:05,959
If he is willing to call, that proves he still has a conscience.

196
00:18:05,959 --> 00:18:09,119
Just wait patiently and he'll certainly show up.

197
00:18:09,119 --> 00:18:10,935
Don't be anxious.

198
00:18:32,940 --> 00:18:36,423
Go get some rest. I'll wash the rest.

199
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:43,579
Go get some sleep. Leave the rest to me.

200
00:18:51,620 --> 00:18:53,930
What's wrong? Are you hungry?

201
00:18:55,219 --> 00:18:58,619
Are you hungry? I'll go make some food.

202
00:18:58,619 --> 00:19:01,379
That would be too loud. It might wake him.

203
00:19:01,379 --> 00:19:03,002
Just wait.

204
00:19:20,659 --> 00:19:22,440
Just leave it.

205
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:24,419
Move the backpack away.

206
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:27,985
Be quiet.

207
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:36,939
Where did you get that?

208
00:19:36,939 --> 00:19:39,200
It's combat readiness food.

209
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:41,640
I've been at war with him for so many years.

210
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:44,079
Of course, I have to be prepared.

211
00:19:44,613 --> 00:19:47,403
Just eat it. Go on.

212
00:20:00,534 --> 00:20:02,120
- It's your turn.
- I'm not hungry.

213
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,685
- You eat some.
- I'm not hungry.

214
00:20:03,685 --> 00:20:05,305
Yummy.

215
00:20:05,305 --> 00:20:07,000
Yummy.

216
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,048
I really don't want to eat it.

217
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:23,380
Wait, save some for me.

218
00:20:23,380 --> 00:20:26,140
I let you eat, and you're really wolfing it down.

219
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:29,200
Jeez.

220
00:20:50,119 --> 00:20:52,219
Wait. It's okay. Bear with it.

221
00:20:52,219 --> 00:20:54,819
Come on.

222
00:20:54,819 --> 00:20:56,732
Oh, my God.

223
00:20:56,732 --> 00:21:00,800
How do you feel? How do you feel?

224
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:04,060
Oh, God. You're soaking in sweat from the pain.

225
00:21:05,639 --> 00:21:09,220
I'm fine. Go back to sleep.

226
00:21:09,220 --> 00:21:11,759
What sleep? Let's go to the hospital.

227
00:21:11,759 --> 00:21:12,979
How can you go back to sleep?

228
00:21:12,979 --> 00:21:15,359
It's really serious. Don't sleep now.

229
00:21:15,359 --> 00:21:17,682
Keep your voice down.

230
00:21:17,682 --> 00:21:19,020
Don't wake the kids.

231
00:21:19,020 --> 00:21:21,899
Got it. Put your clothes on now.

232
00:21:26,939 --> 00:21:29,900
Jin Beibei, let me officially notify you.

233
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:34,219
Starting tomorrow, you'll be a beautiful seventeen-year-old girl.

234
00:21:34,219 --> 00:21:37,139
Sis, why are you posing before you wash your face?

235
00:21:37,139 --> 00:21:39,000
None of your business.

236
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,340
Mom and Dad left.

237
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:42,162
What?

238
00:21:42,162 --> 00:21:44,490
[Beibei: Your dad and I are going back to our hometown.]

239
00:21:44,490 --> 00:21:47,240
[We'll be back tomorrow. Take care of Doudou.]

240
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:49,060
They are so unreliable!

241
00:21:49,060 --> 00:21:52,219
Why are they going back to their hometown now?

242
00:21:52,699 --> 00:21:54,100
They just left a note?

243
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:56,554
They didn't even leave any money?

244
00:21:56,554 --> 00:21:58,039
I want to eat fried dough sticks.

245
00:21:58,039 --> 00:22:01,419
You look like fried dough sticks. Eat the note.

246
00:22:19,060 --> 00:22:22,100
You two behaved pretty well this morning.

247
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:23,279
Sit down.

248
00:22:23,279 --> 00:22:26,140
I'm so hungry.

249
00:22:26,140 --> 00:22:27,694
However,

250
00:22:28,939 --> 00:22:32,219
every family has their own rules.

251
00:22:32,219 --> 00:22:34,939
We'll put this matter behind us.

252
00:22:34,939 --> 00:22:36,419
Never do this again.

253
00:22:36,419 --> 00:22:38,459
- Do you hear me?
- We hear you.

254
00:22:38,459 --> 00:22:39,829
Eat.

255
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:44,100
Uncle Gao, you're having breakfast?

256
00:22:44,939 --> 00:22:46,525
What's going on?

257
00:22:49,300 --> 00:22:51,519
Look at them.

258
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:56,639
They are like bandits.

259
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,720
Doudou, where are your parents?

260
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:05,351
I don't know. They went back to their hometown.

261
00:23:05,351 --> 00:23:07,187
Back to their hometown?

262
00:23:07,187 --> 00:23:08,380
When did they decide to do that?

263
00:23:08,380 --> 00:23:11,800
I don't know. They were gone when we woke up.

264
00:23:12,979 --> 00:23:14,140
When are they coming back?

265
00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:15,659
I want to ask them the same thing.

266
00:23:15,659 --> 00:23:18,599
They don't remember anything important!

267
00:23:29,620 --> 00:23:31,351
Are you all right?

268
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:36,259
W-What are you doing?

269
00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:40,380
It's okay. I can do it myself.

270
00:23:40,380 --> 00:23:44,119
What do you mean you're okay? Last night wasn't scary enough?

271
00:23:45,459 --> 00:23:47,340
Eat slowly.

272
00:23:47,919 --> 00:23:49,907
Have Doudou and Beibei eaten yet?

273
00:23:49,907 --> 00:23:51,459
You're already in this condition.

274
00:23:51,459 --> 00:23:53,300
Why are you still worried about them?

275
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:58,559
All right, don't worry about it. I'll call Bin in a little while and ask him to care for them, okay?

276
00:23:58,559 --> 00:24:00,259
Don't bother Bin anymore.

277
00:24:00,259 --> 00:24:02,219
He's having enough trouble at home.

278
00:24:02,219 --> 00:24:05,759
When should we bother Bin if we don't do it now?

279
00:24:05,759 --> 00:24:07,380
How about this?

280
00:24:07,380 --> 00:24:09,419
I'll tell Beibei to come. Beibei has grown up now,

281
00:24:09,419 --> 00:24:11,219
she should help out around the house.

282
00:24:11,219 --> 00:24:12,580
Don't bring her here.

283
00:24:12,580 --> 00:24:14,022
It's her birthday tomorrow.

284
00:24:14,022 --> 00:24:16,699
Don't let her know I'm in the hospital.

285
00:24:16,699 --> 00:24:18,520
I knew you were in the hospital!

286
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:20,860
Wait, how did you find out? Do they all know?

287
00:24:20,860 --> 00:24:22,197
Jin, what happened to you?

288
00:24:22,197 --> 00:24:23,240
What do you mean what happened?

289
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:26,520
It was so scary last night. Let me tell you, he was awakened by chest pains last night.

290
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:29,519
I gave him some Quick Acting Heart Relievers and took him here.

291
00:24:29,519 --> 00:24:31,060
He refused to come.

292
00:24:31,060 --> 00:24:32,259
What did the doctor say?

293
00:24:32,259 --> 00:24:35,485
The doctor said there's a problem with his cardiac valves. It's best to do surgery.

294
00:24:35,485 --> 00:24:38,640
I'm not doing surgery. Tomorrow is Beibei's birthday. I have to celebrate her birthday.

295
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:40,599
Is Beibei's birthday more important than your life?

296
00:24:40,599 --> 00:24:43,140
Mrs. Jin, Jin, here's the deal.

297
00:24:43,140 --> 00:24:44,259
Don't worry about the kids.

298
00:24:44,259 --> 00:24:45,480
Xiaowen and Yang are watching them.

299
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:48,499
Jin, just stay here and do a full exam, okay?

300
00:24:48,499 --> 00:24:49,659
Is that okay?

301
00:24:49,659 --> 00:24:50,659
I don't care.

302
00:24:50,659 --> 00:24:53,839
I have to go home tomorrow to celebrate Beibei's birthday.

303
00:24:53,839 --> 00:24:55,318
You...

304
00:24:57,739 --> 00:24:59,780
Don't peek.

305
00:24:59,780 --> 00:25:02,260
Got it. Bye.

306
00:25:07,140 --> 00:25:08,499
What did he say?

307
00:25:08,499 --> 00:25:10,999
Gao Bin said he has to take care of something in school. He's not coming home today.

308
00:25:10,999 --> 00:25:12,820
The four of us will spend the day together.

309
00:25:12,820 --> 00:25:15,179
Is it my turn? Three, four, five, six, seven, straight.

310
00:25:15,179 --> 00:25:17,180
Adults are all unreliable.

311
00:25:17,180 --> 00:25:18,900
Can anyone beat that?

312
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:20,860
What are you guys doing tomorrow?

313
00:25:20,860 --> 00:25:23,580
What can we do? I'm too tired. I'll stay in bed.

314
00:25:23,580 --> 00:25:24,900
I need to train.

315
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:26,219
What are you doing tomorrow?

316
00:25:26,219 --> 00:25:27,400
Going to the planetarium.

317
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,119
You can't afford to go to the planetarium!

318
00:25:29,119 --> 00:25:30,699
I have money.

319
00:25:30,699 --> 00:25:33,240
Where did you get that? Didn't you say Mom and Dad didn't leave us money?

320
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:35,060
Mom and Dad left me money.

321
00:25:35,060 --> 00:25:37,000
Give it back to me.

322
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:38,140
Stop fighting.

323
00:25:38,140 --> 00:25:40,004
Hurry up, can you beat the straight?

324
00:25:40,004 --> 00:25:41,459
No.

325
00:25:41,459 --> 00:25:43,540
No? None of you can beat that?

326
00:25:43,540 --> 00:25:44,939
Are you sure?

327
00:25:44,939 --> 00:25:47,196
A pair of jokers.

328
00:25:47,196 --> 00:25:48,900
So boring. I'm not playing anymore.

329
00:25:48,900 --> 00:25:50,659
What do you mean?

330
00:25:50,659 --> 00:25:52,340
You're not playing after you lose?

331
00:25:52,340 --> 00:25:54,499
You're such a sore loser.

332
00:25:55,340 --> 00:25:56,820
- Hey, Handsome.
- Want a haircut?

333
00:25:56,820 --> 00:25:57,839
I'm here for Zhao Jiabao.

334
00:25:57,839 --> 00:25:59,060
Jiabao?

335
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:01,800
Jiabao, someone's here for you!

336
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:03,740
Coming!

337
00:26:07,060 --> 00:26:08,300
Piao.

338
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:10,080
Hao, wash the towels.

339
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:11,140
Okay!

340
00:26:11,140 --> 00:26:12,975
What is it?

341
00:26:16,940 --> 00:26:18,419
That's it?

342
00:26:18,419 --> 00:26:21,259
What do you know? This is the latest version.

343
00:26:21,860 --> 00:26:23,245
I'll give you fifty.

344
00:26:23,245 --> 00:26:24,780
I spent over two hundred.

345
00:26:24,780 --> 00:26:26,560
Why aren't you keeping them then?

346
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:28,470
It's none of your business.

347
00:26:29,340 --> 00:26:30,739
How about a hundred?

348
00:26:30,739 --> 00:26:33,100
A hundred?

349
00:26:38,060 --> 00:26:40,449
Here's ninety. Are you selling it or not?

350
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:45,380
You owe me ten yuan.

351
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:48,000
Are you saving up for another singing contest?

352
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,780
What does that have to do with you?

353
00:26:49,780 --> 00:26:51,786
Leave if you don't want a haircut.

354
00:26:56,460 --> 00:27:00,140
[2005 Calendar]

355
00:27:25,460 --> 00:27:28,470
[Beibei: Your dad and I are going back to our hometown. We'll be back tomorrow. Take care of Doudou.]

356
00:27:59,620 --> 00:28:01,320
Doudou.

357
00:28:05,219 --> 00:28:07,034
Doudou.

358
00:28:08,140 --> 00:28:12,800
Little b*stard, where did he go so early in the morning?

359
00:28:16,042 --> 00:28:18,562
[We went out to play. Eat by yourself!]

360
00:28:25,499 --> 00:28:26,769
Whatever.

361
00:28:26,769 --> 00:28:28,459
Go wherever you want.

362
00:28:28,459 --> 00:28:30,860
My birthday isn't important anyway.

363
00:28:32,100 --> 00:28:33,562
I'll eat.

364
00:28:41,459 --> 00:28:46,179
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

365
00:28:46,179 --> 00:28:50,580
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

366
00:28:50,580 --> 00:28:55,499
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

367
00:28:55,499 --> 00:28:59,640
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

368
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:04,280
Happy birthday, Beibei!

369
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:06,880
How do you guys know it's my birthday?

370
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:08,000
None of us forgot it.

371
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:10,679
We were trying to surprise you.

372
00:29:10,679 --> 00:29:15,580
Sis, I took the money because I wanted to buy you a cake.

373
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:21,780
My super sweet brother Dou.

374
00:29:21,780 --> 00:29:24,740
Wait, Meng, aren't you grounded?

375
00:29:24,740 --> 00:29:29,419
I never left the house since the beginning of summer just for today.

376
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:32,000
Jia, what about you?

377
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:33,780
Aren't you in the boot camp?

378
00:29:33,780 --> 00:29:37,260
I just came back and I came to celebrate your birthday.

379
00:29:37,260 --> 00:29:41,179
By the way, this is the present Meng and I bought you.

380
00:29:42,140 --> 00:29:45,340
Sisters are the best!

381
00:29:46,340 --> 00:29:47,620
What are you whining about?

382
00:29:47,620 --> 00:29:50,720
Zhao Jiabao, did you come empty-handed?

383
00:29:53,079 --> 00:29:55,118
That's right.

384
00:29:55,118 --> 00:29:56,836
Here you go.

385
00:29:57,700 --> 00:29:59,320
All right, all right. Cut the cake now.

386
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:00,660
Wait a minute.

387
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:02,719
Let me go dress up.

388
00:30:02,719 --> 00:30:04,100
You're showing off now.

389
00:30:04,100 --> 00:30:06,205
No peeking!

390
00:30:06,205 --> 00:30:07,744
Hurry up.

391
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:14,560
B-Beibei, m-make a wish.

392
00:30:14,560 --> 00:30:15,599
That's right.

393
00:30:15,599 --> 00:30:17,180
Make a nice wish.

394
00:30:28,499 --> 00:30:31,760
Beibei, what happened?

395
00:30:32,559 --> 00:30:34,392
What's wrong?

396
00:30:43,019 --> 00:30:46,760
I'm telling you,

397
00:30:47,659 --> 00:30:51,780
a few days ago, my mom told me

398
00:30:51,780 --> 00:30:55,580
my dad prepared a birthday gift for me.

399
00:30:55,580 --> 00:31:01,040
But none of them remembered my birthday!

400
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:04,100
No, Beibei, Principal Jin must be busy with something.

401
00:31:04,100 --> 00:31:07,100
No.

402
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:11,360
My dad was really busy when I was little,

403
00:31:11,360 --> 00:31:17,380
but he would always come home to celebrate my birthday.

404
00:31:17,380 --> 00:31:20,380
I don't know what happened today.

405
00:31:20,380 --> 00:31:24,799
Now that I grew up, I'm no longer important to him.

406
00:31:24,799 --> 00:31:27,079
That's not the case, Beibei.

407
00:31:27,079 --> 00:31:28,680
That's not the case.

408
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:29,799
Beibei, Beibei.

409
00:31:29,799 --> 00:31:31,119
I-I...

410
00:31:31,119 --> 00:31:35,960
Beibei, I heard if you cry on your birthday, you'd get pockmarks on your face.

411
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:36,979
It's really scary.

412
00:31:36,979 --> 00:31:40,529
That's right, you'll get wrinkles around your eyes too.

413
00:31:42,359 --> 00:31:43,720
Don't cry. Don't cry.

414
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:45,200
I'm sorry. I made it up.

415
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,599
D-Don't cry.

416
00:31:46,599 --> 00:31:48,224
Tissue, Meng. Tissue.

417
00:31:48,224 --> 00:31:50,680
- Here, wipe your tears.
- Comfort her.

418
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:52,820
Your wish won't come true if you keep crying.

419
00:31:52,820 --> 00:31:55,620
That's right. Your wish won't come true.

420
00:32:12,699 --> 00:32:18,260
♪ The white city, the gray wallpaper ♪

421
00:32:19,319 --> 00:32:25,479
♪ The night sky after shooting stars have left ♪

422
00:32:27,060 --> 00:32:32,300
♪ The warm shadows fading in the night ♪

423
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:40,559
♪ We laugh and ramble about so many interesting things in our future ♪

424
00:32:41,680 --> 00:32:47,939
♪ The wasted times we went through together ♪

425
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:55,100
♪ Nobody else were there, only us, and that's why it's so beautiful ♪

426
00:32:56,119 --> 00:33:01,559
♪ If you were to ask me where my future would be ♪

427
00:33:02,219 --> 00:33:10,059
♪ How much courage it would take to live in the same city with you ♪

428
00:33:10,819 --> 00:33:16,079
♪ That's an untold story ♪

429
00:33:16,079 --> 00:33:24,640
♪ And an inexistent name ♪

430
00:33:24,640 --> 00:33:30,900
♪ What I want is the story to stop where it should stop ♪

431
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:35,239
♪ Far away and stupidly ♪

432
00:33:36,119 --> 00:33:43,879
♪ Staring but refraining ♪

433
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:49,979
Beibei, you still have us.

434
00:34:06,860 --> 00:34:10,560
Principal Jin isn't home on such an important day for Beibei.

435
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:12,360
Did something happen to him?

436
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:13,860
That's not possible.

437
00:34:13,860 --> 00:34:16,840
Didn't Principal Jin say he went back to his hometown?

438
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:18,939
He usually lets us take care of each other.

439
00:34:18,939 --> 00:34:20,519
We're already used to it.

440
00:34:20,519 --> 00:34:22,260
Come on, have a strawberry.

441
00:34:22,260 --> 00:34:23,619
Come on.

442
00:34:23,619 --> 00:34:24,939
This one.

443
00:34:24,939 --> 00:34:26,816
How's that? Is it sweet?

444
00:34:30,019 --> 00:34:33,580
Zhao Jiabao, why did you give me a pen?

445
00:34:34,199 --> 00:34:36,225
Let me see.

446
00:34:38,879 --> 00:34:42,760
This pen has a 14k gold tip.

447
00:34:42,760 --> 00:34:45,059
Someone gave it to me. I didn't care to use it.

448
00:34:45,059 --> 00:34:49,500
If you use a g-gold pen on your exam, would you pass it?

449
00:34:49,500 --> 00:34:53,280
That depends on who's using it. People who do not study hard don't deserve such a nice pen.

450
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:55,820
Fine, you're all hinting at me, right?

451
00:34:55,820 --> 00:34:58,519
Starting tomorrow, I'll work hard to show all of you.

452
00:34:58,519 --> 00:35:03,039
"I hope these headphones can improve your taste."

453
00:35:03,039 --> 00:35:04,380
What headphones?

454
00:35:04,380 --> 00:35:06,840
I wrote it wrong.

455
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:09,502
Are you unwrapping presents? Do it now.

456
00:35:14,780 --> 00:35:16,220
What's wrong?

457
00:35:16,220 --> 00:35:21,000
Don't open it in front of the boys.

458
00:35:21,499 --> 00:35:23,492
It's fine!

459
00:35:24,539 --> 00:35:27,059
Go look at it in your room later. It's a surprise.

460
00:35:27,059 --> 00:35:28,519
What is it?

461
00:35:28,519 --> 00:35:31,720
J-Just... just listen to us.

462
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:34,260
What is it?

463
00:35:35,740 --> 00:35:40,841
A bra, with pads, for enhancement.

464
00:35:41,639 --> 00:35:43,422
What enhancement?

465
00:35:45,260 --> 00:35:46,700
Eat the cake.

466
00:35:46,700 --> 00:35:48,599
- Hurry up.
- Slow down.

467
00:35:48,599 --> 00:35:49,679
Are you finished yet?

468
00:35:49,679 --> 00:35:50,899
Just a few more signatures. It'll be done right away.

469
00:35:50,899 --> 00:35:53,260
Hurry up! Beibei's birthday is about to pass!

470
00:35:53,260 --> 00:35:55,919
You just got discharged. What's the rush?

471
00:35:55,919 --> 00:35:57,720
By the way, did you buy a birthday cake?

472
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:59,619
I've been so busy. When do I have time for that?

473
00:35:59,619 --> 00:36:02,080
- Later.
- We'll buy one.

474
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:04,280
Fine, if you guys won't buy it, I'll go buy it!

475
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:06,760
You just got discharged. Don't do that. I'll go buy it.

476
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:08,342
All right, thank you.

477
00:36:08,342 --> 00:36:10,000
Jin! Jin! Doctor! Doctor!

478
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:12,139
- Jin!
- Doctor! Doctor!

479
00:36:12,139 --> 00:36:15,322
- Jin! Jin!
- Jin!

480
00:36:26,880 --> 00:36:40,600
''Wings to Fly to the Future'' - Yang Feitong

481
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:46,690
♫  I know the direction of dawn  ♫

482
00:36:46,690 --> 00:36:54,055
♫  It's right in front of me, waiting for me to shine  ♫

483
00:36:54,055 --> 00:36:59,945
♫ Starlight shines along the way ♫

484
00:36:59,945 --> 00:37:05,985
♫  The starlight that shines alone the way  ♫

485
00:37:05,985 --> 00:37:12,537
♫  Accompanying me on my adventure, packing my dreams in my heart  ♫

486
00:37:12,537 --> 00:37:18,277
♫  Maybe I'm not destined for the hardship of this journey  ♫

487
00:37:18,277 --> 00:37:22,190
♫  And chase after the longing in my heart  ♫

488
00:37:22,190 --> 00:37:25,612
♫  Let set sail on your dreams  ♫

489
00:37:25,612 --> 00:37:28,907
♫  Let's not have any regrets in our youth  ♫

490
00:37:28,907 --> 00:37:35,667
♫  Even if you stumble and fall, you'll have me by your side  ♫

491
00:37:35,667 --> 00:37:38,878
♫  Let's find the answer through the madness  ♫

492
00:37:38,878 --> 00:37:43,090
♫  Let's have courage to ride the waves and billows  ♫

493
00:37:43,090 --> 00:37:46,910
♫  With my wings, I'll fly us to the future  ♫

494
00:37:46,910 --> 00:37:54,770
♫  And step forward into the future without fear of sorrow  ♫
